In England, in the seven days to 23 November, there were 247,602 new confirmed cases (437.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 November, there were 232,813 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 6% (14,789 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 28 November is 8,605,284 (15,217.1 cases per 100,000 population).
